# Cosmic Ocean: UI/UX Bible (V1)

*This document defines the strict visual design system, accessibility standards, and user experience rules for all 2D HTML/CSS overlays in Cosmic Ocean. It supersedes previous documents regarding UX pacing and control locks.*

---

## 1. Visual Design System

The UI must feel premium, lightweight, and highly readable. We avoid excessive glassmorphism to ensure text clarity and rendering performance.

### 1.1 Design Tokens

These values are the single source of truth for the entire application, enabling rapid future redesigns.

```css
:root {
  /* Colors */
  --color-bg: #0A0F1D;
  --color-text: #F0F4F8;
  --color-accent: #00F0FF;
  --color-success: #FF00E5;
  --color-muted: #9BA4B5;
  --color-border: #1E2638;

  /* Spacing */
  --space-1: 4px;
  --space-2: 8px;
  --space-3: 16px;
  --space-4: 24px;
  --space-5: 32px;

  /* Border Radius */
  --radius-sm: 4px;
  --radius-md: 8px;
}
```

### 1.2 Typography
We use a high-contrast sans-serif pairing that reads perfectly on all screen sizes.
*   **Headings:** `Outfit` (Bold, geometric, modern).
*   **Body & UI Text:** `Inter` (Highly legible, excellent for long-form case studies).
*   **Monospace (Code blocks):** `Fira Code`.

